beer.beer_description: Two worlds collide with this single malt, single hop IPA using a uniquely expressively breed of Centennial hops grown by Ryefield in Bemboka NSW. The malt base is a 100% Isaria 1924 Pilsner malt, which is made from Germany's oldest malting barley variety Isaria, an heirloom grain. Big bright citrus and melon notes brought by NSW grown hops. Supported by a minimal malty-sweet base. Enjoy!
